- Blockchain was invented to support Bitcoin.
- Ledgers: a note book to keep records of all releated transactions.
  - need a trusted & 3rd-party record to avoid fraud, disagreement.
  - cost money, might be delay.
- Distributed Ledgers:
  - automatically copied to all personal ledgers when new transaction is made.
  - decentralized
  - peer-to-peer replication
- Every blocks is used with cryptographic hash.
  - can't get orginal data back.
  - compare if data is tampering by comparing hash value.
- new block contains previous block hash value in its data.
- Type of blockchain:
  - Public vs Private
  - Permissioned (business blockchain) vs Permissionless (typical for currency,
    open platforms)
- Smart Contracts:
